# What is the role of the International Atomic Energy Agency in the Russia-Ukraine conflict?

## Summary
The International Atomic Energy Agency is working to establish a safety and security zone around the Zaporizhzhia nuclear power plant in Ukraine, which has been damaged by shelling during the conflict. IAEA Director General Rafael Mariano Grossi is currently in Ukraine for talks with the government on this issue. Russia has seized control of the plant director, which jeopardizes the safety of the plant and could lead to a nuclear accident.

